feat: simpler setup email steps and narrower filter query

The setup email now assumes the user is reading it in Gmail desktop and
opens with a one-click link straight to the filter settings page, dropping
the redundant 'Open Gmail / Settings / See all settings' preamble. Steps
shrink from 6 to 4.

The Gmail filter query now uses a narrow OTP-only subject exclusion list
(FILTER_OTP_SUBJECTS, 9 entries) instead of the full IGNORE_SUBJECTS (30+).
The bot already drops non-transaction noise server-side; the user-facing
filter only needs to keep OTPs / auth codes from being auto-forwarded
(security-sensitive). Side effect: the pasted query is short enough to
visually scan.

Test for buildGmailFilterQuery updated to match.
